						<div class="postbody">I just implemented iNES mapper 118: Goal 2, Pro Sport Hockey, Armadillo, Ys 3, NES Play Action Football.
<br />
<br />I'm having problems getting Ys 3 and Goal 2 run correctly, both have their status screens shaking vertically by 1 line, making me think IRQ handling is the suspect. But, none of the other MMC3 games are having any IRQ problems anymore (of the ones I've tested, and that's a lot). So I was wondering, does this mapper use a different IRQ mechanism ?</div>

