				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Ah, I found the cause: My MMC3 IRQ handler gets called whenever there's a PPU read or write, so when there's a delay between two accesses, the 2nd access might get interpreted as a valid rising edge when it wasn't, 'refreshing' the handler constantly fixed Goal 2.
<br />
<br />Strangely, I haven't seen this bug affecting other MMC3 games.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

