				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Sep 19, 2004 10:59 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 1421
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The MMC3 waits for PPU A12 to be low for at least <em>n</em> cycles in a row before it will recognize an additional rising edge. If it were the latter (ignore A12 for <em>n</em> cycles after a rising edge), then n would have to be VERY high to prevent it from messing up when background tiles are in the upper pattern table (since this would cause 34 rising edges in a row, and only the FIRST one is detected).
<br />
<br />By manually toggling PPU A12 (by writing to $2006), the MMC3 will decrement the counter on every rising edge, so the absolute maximum delay is 9 CPU cycles (around 13 complete PPU memory accesses).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

